## Cover Letter (`cover-letter.txt`)

- Starts with BROCCOLI (no quotes, no asterisks). First word, first line.
- All three screening questions answered inline (Q1: Bonhams Next.js / Playwright /_next/data; Q2: stack reasoning with no Scrapy rationale; Q3: rate-limiting discipline and never-blocked policy).
- U.S. Bank Python backend ownership called out explicitly (600-user platform, 60k LOC, sole SME within two months).
- Playwright and Puppeteer scraping history named directly.
- Demo link: https://michaelwegter.com/demos/auction-scraper/ (appears twice: once in the hook, once at close).
- GitHub link: https://github.com/mwegter95
- Positioned as scraping specialist, not full-stack generalist.
- No em/en dashes. No filler or preamble. Michael's voice.
- Word count: ~430 words (skimmable).

---

## One-Pager (`one-pager.html`)

Design: auction-catalog/fine-art-house aesthetic. Cormorant Garamond display serif, Inter body. Palette: ivory (#F8F5EF) background, charcoal (#1A1814), oxblood (#6B1A1A) accent, gilt (#A8842C) labels. Zero em/en dashes.

Sections:
1. Header (name, role, location, GitHub, portfolio)
2. Demo hero panel (dark, gilt accent, CTA button linking to live demo, demo URL)
3. Screenshot strip: 3 of the 5 captured media files (initial, mid-stream, JSON export)
4. Pipeline tool judgment table: 3 sources x (tool / site type / rationale)
5. Screening Q&A (3 blocks, gilt left-border rule)
6. Proof cards grid (2x2): U.S. Bank TDAAS / Playwright+Puppeteer / Optum current contract / communication/location
7. Skills tags: Python, Playwright, Puppeteer, BeautifulSoup, requests/httpx, asyncio, JSON normalization, ETL pipelines, Flask, SQL, Azure, React
8. Footer: name + GitHub / Portfolio / Live Demo links

Screenshot paths use relative `media/` prefix (correct since the file sits in the run directory alongside the media/ folder).

---

## Deck (`deck.pptx`)

7 slides, 13.33 x 7.5 in (widescreen). Auction-catalog palette applied via python-pptx (ivory background, charcoal/oxblood/gilt accent, Georgia serif for display, Calibri body). No em/en dashes.

| Slide | Title |
|---|---|
| 1 | Cover: name, role, demo + GitHub URLs |
| 2 | Live Demo: what it does, 6 feature bullets, demo URL |
| 3 | Tool Judgment: 3 source cards (tool, site type, rationale) + normalized schema fields |
| 4 | Responsible Scraping: 6 practice cards (crawl-delay, jitter, robots.txt, backoff, flagging, telemetry) |
| 5 | Why Michael: 4 proof cards (U.S. Bank, Playwright/Puppeteer, Optum, communication) |
| 6 | Screening Q&A: 3 full answers in bordered blocks |
| 7 | Next Steps: CTA, three links, location/language/camera-on tagline |

